<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>He has so far stayed mum on rumours that he is set to join the cast of the upcoming series of hit ITV competition Dancing On Ice.</p>

<p>But Jason Donovan had more bothersome matters on his mind on Wednesday, when he was spotted getting caught in the rain during a solo stroll through London.</p>

<p>The 52-year-old actor looked decidedly unimpressed as he was caught in the downpour, signalling the end of the capital's unseasonably balmy weather.</p>

<p>Rain, rain, go away: Jason Donovan was spotted getting caught in the rain during a solo stroll through London on Wednesday, amid rumours he's set to compete on Dancing On Ice</p>

<p>The former Neighbours star was seen looking looking at properties in an estate agent's window, before he attempted to run for cover amid the torrential rain.</p>

<p>Australian actor Jason looked casually cool for the solo outing, donning a baggy light grey sweater with black shorts, which he teamed with white running shoes. </p>

<p>Jason was spotted last week with a gash on his forehead amid rumours he is set to star in the 2021 series of Dancing On Ice. </p>

<p>Unimpressed: The 52-year-old actor looked decidedly unimpressed as he was caught in the downpour, signalling the end of the capital's unseasonably balmy weather</p>

<p>The former Neighbours heartthrob - who competed on Strictly Come Dancing in 2011 - is expected to join the star-studded line-up on the show when it airs in January.</p>

<p>A source told The Sun: 'Jason is a great signing for the show as he has plenty of star power.</p>

<p>'He knows how to dance but if he thinks it’ll be any help once he’s on the ice he has another thing coming. </p>

<p>'He’s hoping to rank higher in this show than he did on Strictly, he just needs to find out if he can stay upright once he has his skates on.'</p>

<p>MailOnline has contacted Jason's representatives for comment. </p>

<p>Show: Myleene Klass was the first to confirm that she would be appearing on the show in 2021</p>

<p>So far, Denise Van Outen, Myleene Klass, and Emmerdale's Joe Warren Plant are among the first celebrities to have been confirmed for the series.</p>

<p>Myleene confirmed her participation at the start of the week, telling her Instagram followers: 'Guess who won’t be holding the coats at the side of the rink anymore!</p>

<p>'I am so, SO excited to be joining the cast of <?php echo e('@'); ?>dancingonice. My girls have always wanted me to do this but I’ve always been too scared someone will skate over my fingers!</p>

<p>Anyway, I want to make them proud and show them I’m up for a challenge when completely out of my comfort zone but most of all, I want a bum like Jlo!'</p>

<p>Confirmed: West End star Denise Van Outen has also been confirmed, after relentless rumours</p>
